This paper discusses the energy efficiency of cellular networks for IoT connectivity, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networked Systems and Communication) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses data processing and transmission, which can be related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The paper proposes a scheme to reduce power consumption, which can be related to control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the reduction of data size, which can be related to computer engineering, making cs.CE (Computer Engineering) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses security issues related to IoT, which can be related to cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible sub-category.
